tion":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the personal name   Robert  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is also occasionally borne by Jews, presumably as an Americanized form of some similar (like-sounding) Jewish surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Robert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Gilles, Normand, Armand, Lucien, Pierre, Emile, Michel, Edouard, Gaston, Yves.","French, Walloon, English, German, Dutch, Flemish, and Breton (of French origin); Hungarian (<b>Róbert</b>): from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Ro(d)bert</i> (Middle English <i>Robert</i>, Old French <i>Ro(d)bert</i>), composed of the elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame, renown’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This is found occasionally in Anglo-Saxon England before the Conquest, but in the main it was introduced into England by the Normans and quickly became popular among all classes of society. Pet forms and diminutives are found from an early date,   Robin   being particularly common. Compare   Robair  ,   Robar  ,   Robare  , and   Rober  .","In some cases also an Americanized form of one or more similar (like-sounding) Jewish surnames."]},{"name":"Robers","meanings":["English: variant of   Roberts  ."]},{"name":"Roberds","meanings":["English: variant of   Roberts  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Robards","meanings":["English (Kent): variant of   Roberts  ."]},{"name":"Robarts","meanings":["English (Bedfordshire and Hertfortshire): variant of   Roberts  ."]}]},{"name":"Stephen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English spelling of the name of the first Christian martyr (Acts 6–7), whose feast is accordingly celebrated next after Christ's own (  26 December ). His name is derived from the Greek word <i>stephanos</i> ‘garland, crown’."],"variants":[{"name":"Stephan","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , preserving the vowels of the Greek name."]},{"name":"Steven","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , reflecting the normal pronunciation of the name in the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Stephen Roberts was born in 1350, in Cranbrook, Kent, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Robertes. He married Johane Tilley in 1408, in Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1440, in Cranbrook, Kent, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 90."},"et":{"1350–1440":"1350–1440","1358–1430":"1358–1430","1380–1430":"1380–1430","1408–1460":"1408–1460","1410–1499":"1410–1499","1350–1441":"1350–1441","about 1408":"umbes 1408","1358":"1358","1499":"1499","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","about 1410":"umbes 1410","1408":"1408","1380":"1380","Glassenbury Manor, Cranbrook, Kent, England":"Cranbrook, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1350–1440":"1350–1440","1358–1430":"1358–1430","1380–1430":"1380–1430","1408–1460":"1408–1460","1410–1499":"1410–1499","1350–1441":"1350–1441","about 1408":"noin 1408","1358":"1358","1499":"1499","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","about 1410":"noin 1410","1408":"1408","1380":"1380","Glassenbury Manor, Cranbrook, Kent, England":"Cranbrook, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1350–1440":"1350–1440","1358–1430":"1358–1430","1380–1430":"1380–1430","1408–1460":"1408–1460","1410–1499":"1410–1499","1350–1441":"1350–1441","about 1408":"environ 1408","1358":"1358","1499":"1499","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","about 1410":"environ 1410","1408":"1408","1380":"1380","Glassenbury Manor, 